  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: dd64eb842f3dd694bae8487ce6510215, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Naomi Widowed'
      title: Naomi Widowed
      number: 1
      content: '  In the days when the judges ruled there was a famine in the land,
        and a man of Bethlehem in Judah went to sojourn in the country of Moab, he
        and his wife and his two sons. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The name of the man was Elimelech and the name of his wife Naomi,
        and the names of his two sons were Mahlon and Chilion. They were Ephrathites
        from Bethlehem in Judah. They went into the country of Moab and remained
        there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'But Elimelech, the husband of Naomi, died, and she was left with
        her two sons. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'These took Moabite wives; the name of the one was Orpah and the name
        of the other Ruth. They lived there about ten years, '
      comments: []
    - name: "5: Ruth\u2019s Loyalty to Naomi"
      title: "Ruth\u2019s Loyalty to Naomi"
      number: 5
      content: 'and both Mahlon and Chilion died, so that the woman was left without
        her two sons and her husband.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then she arose with her daughters-in-law to return from the country
        of Moab, for she had heard in the fields of Moab that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had visited his people and given them food. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So she set out from the place where she was with her two daughters-in-law,
        and they went on the way to return to the land of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But Naomi said to her two daughters-in-law, \u201CGo, return each
        of you to her mother\u2019s house. May the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  deal
        kindly with you, as you have dealt with the dead and with me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> grant that you may find rest, each
        of you in the house of her husband!\u201D Then she kissed them, and they
        lifted up their voices and wept. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And they said to her, \u201CNo, we will return with you to your people.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But Naomi said, \u201CTurn back, my daughters; why will you go with
        me? Have I yet sons in my womb that they may become your husbands? "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Turn back, my daughters; go your way, for I am too old to have a
        husband. If I should say I have hope, even if I should have a husband this
        night and should bear sons, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "would you therefore wait till they were grown? Would you therefore
        refrain from marrying? No, my daughters, for it is exceedingly bitter to
        me for your sake that the hand of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has gone
        out against me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then they lifted up their voices and wept again. And Orpah kissed
        her mother-in-law, but Ruth clung to her.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And she said, \u201CSee, your sister-in-law has gone back to her
        people and to her gods; return after your sister-in-law.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "But Ruth said, \u201CDo not urge me to leave you or to return from
        following you. For where you go I will go, and where you lodge I will lodge.
        Your people shall be my people, and your God my God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Where you die I will die, and there will I be buried. May the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        do so to me and more also if anything but death parts me from you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: Naomi and Ruth Return'
      title: Naomi and Ruth Return
      number: 18
      content: 'And when Naomi saw that she was determined to go with her, she said
        no more.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "So the two of them went on until they came to Bethlehem. And when
        they came to Bethlehem, the whole town was stirred because of them. And the
        women said, \u201CIs this Naomi?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "She said to them, \u201CDo not call me Naomi;[[COMMENT(0)]] call
        me Mara, for the Almighty has dealt very bitterly with me. "
      comments:
      - number: '1:20 '
        content: 'means means '
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "I went away full, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has brought
        me back empty. Why call me Naomi, when the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has
        testified against me and the Almighty has brought calamity upon me?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: So Naomi returned, and Ruth the Moabite her daughter-in-law with her,
        who returned from the country of Moab. And they came to Bethlehem at the
        beginning of barley harvest.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Ruth Meets Boaz'
      title: Ruth Meets Boaz
      number: 1
      content: "  Now Naomi had a relative of her husband\u2019s, a worthy man of
        the clan of Elimelech, whose name was Boaz. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And Ruth the Moabite said to Naomi, \u201CLet me go to the field
        and glean among the ears of grain after him in whose sight I shall find favor.\u201D
        And she said to her, \u201CGo, my daughter.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So she set out and went and gleaned in the field after the reapers,
        and she happened to come to the part of the field belonging to Boaz, who
        was of the clan of Elimelech. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And behold, Boaz came from Bethlehem. And he said to the reapers,
        \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> be with you!\u201D And they answered,
        \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> bless you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Boaz said to his young man who was in charge of the reapers,
        \u201CWhose young woman is this?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And the servant who was in charge of the reapers answered, \u201CShe
        is the young Moabite woman, who came back with Naomi from the country of
        Moab. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "She said, \u2018Please let me glean and gather among the sheaves
        after the reapers.\u2019 So she came, and she has continued from early morning
        until now, except for a short rest.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:7 '
        content: Compare Septuagint, Vulgate; the meaning of the Hebrew phrase is
          uncertain
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Boaz said to Ruth, \u201CNow, listen, my daughter, do not go
        to glean in another field or leave this one, but keep close to my young women. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Let your eyes be on the field that they are reaping, and go after
        them. Have I not charged the young men not to touch you? And when you are
        thirsty, go to the vessels and drink what the young men have drawn.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then she fell on her face, bowing to the ground, and said to him,
        \u201CWhy have I found favor in your eyes, that you should take notice of
        me, since I am a foreigner?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But Boaz answered her, \u201CAll that you have done for your mother-in-law
        since the death of your husband has been fully told to me, and how you left
        your father and mother and your native land and came to a people that you
        did not know before. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> repay you for what you have done,
        and a full reward be given you by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God
        of Israel, under whose wings you have come to take refuge!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then she said, \u201CI have found favor in your eyes, my lord, for
        you have comforted me and spoken kindly to your servant, though I am not
        one of your servants.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And at mealtime Boaz said to her, \u201CCome here and eat some bread
        and dip your morsel in the wine.\u201D So she sat beside the reapers, and
        he passed to her roasted grain. And she ate until she was satisfied, and
        she had some left over. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "When she rose to glean, Boaz instructed his young men, saying, \u201CLet
        her glean even among the sheaves, and do not reproach her. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And also pull out some from the bundles for her and leave it for
        her to glean, and do not rebuke her.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So she gleaned in the field until evening. Then she beat out what
        she had gleaned, and it was about an ephah[[COMMENT(0)]] of barley. '
      comments:
      - number: '2:17 '
        content: An was about 3/5 bushel or 22 liters
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And she took it up and went into the city. Her mother-in-law saw
        what she had gleaned. She also brought out and gave her what food she had
        left over after being satisfied. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And her mother-in-law said to her, \u201CWhere did you glean today?
        And where have you worked? Blessed be the man who took notice of you.\u201D
        So she told her mother-in-law with whom she had worked and said, \u201CThe
        man\u2019s name with whom I worked today is Boaz.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And Naomi said to her daughter-in-law, \u201CMay he be blessed by
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, whose kindness has not forsaken the living
        or the dead!\u201D Naomi also said to her, \u201CThe man is a close relative
        of ours, one of our redeemers.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And Ruth the Moabite said, \u201CBesides, he said to me, \u2018You
        shall keep close by my young men until they have finished all my harvest.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And Naomi said to Ruth, her daughter-in-law, \u201CIt is good, my
        daughter, that you go out with his young women, lest in another field you
        be assaulted.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: So she kept close to the young women of Boaz, gleaning until the end
        of the barley and wheat harvests. And she lived with her mother-in-law.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Ruth and Boaz at the Threshing Floor'
      title: Ruth and Boaz at the Threshing Floor
      number: 1
      content: "  Then Naomi her mother-in-law said to her, \u201CMy daughter, should
        I not seek rest for you, that it may be well with you? "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Is not Boaz our relative, with whose young women you were? See, he
        is winnowing barley tonight at the threshing floor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Wash therefore and anoint yourself, and put on your cloak and go
        down to the threshing floor, but do not make yourself known to the man until
        he has finished eating and drinking. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But when he lies down, observe the place where he lies. Then go and
        uncover his feet and lie down, and he will tell you what to do.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And she replied, \u201CAll that you say I will do.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So she went down to the threshing floor and did just as her mother-in-law
        had commanded her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And when Boaz had eaten and drunk, and his heart was merry, he went
        to lie down at the end of the heap of grain. Then she came softly and uncovered
        his feet and lay down. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'At midnight the man was startled and turned over, and behold, a woman
        lay at his feet! '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "He said, \u201CWho are you?\u201D And she answered, \u201CI am Ruth,
        your servant. Spread your wings[[COMMENT(0)]] over your servant, for you
        are a redeemer.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '3:9 '
        content: 'Compare 2:12; the word for can also mean '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And he said, \u201CMay you be blessed by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        my daughter. You have made this last kindness greater than the first in that
        you have not gone after young men, whether poor or rich. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And now, my daughter, do not fear. I will do for you all that you
        ask, for all my fellow townsmen know that you are a worthy woman. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And now it is true that I am a redeemer. Yet there is a redeemer
        nearer than I. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Remain tonight, and in the morning, if he will redeem you, good;
        let him do it. But if he is not willing to redeem you, then, as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        lives, I will redeem you. Lie down until the morning.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So she lay at his feet until the morning, but arose before one could
        recognize another. And he said, \u201CLet it not be known that the woman
        came to the threshing floor.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And he said, \u201CBring the garment you are wearing and hold it
        out.\u201D So she held it, and he measured out six measures of barley and
        put it on her. Then she went into the city. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And when she came to her mother-in-law, she said, \u201CHow did you
        fare, my daughter?\u201D Then she told her all that the man had done for
        her, "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "saying, \u201CThese six measures of barley he gave to me, for he
        said to me, \u2018You must not go back empty-handed to your mother-in-law.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "She replied, \u201CWait, my daughter, until you learn how the matter
        turns out, for the man will not rest but will settle the matter today.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Boaz Redeems Ruth'
      title: Boaz Redeems Ruth
      number: 1
      content: "  Now Boaz had gone up to the gate and sat down there. And behold,
        the redeemer, of whom Boaz had spoken, came by. So Boaz said, \u201CTurn
        aside, friend; sit down here.\u201D And he turned aside and sat down. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And he took ten men of the elders of the city and said, \u201CSit
        down here.\u201D So they sat down. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then he said to the redeemer, \u201CNaomi, who has come back from
        the country of Moab, is selling the parcel of land that belonged to our relative
        Elimelech. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So I thought I would tell you of it and say, \u2018Buy it in the
        presence of those sitting here and in the presence of the elders of my people.\u2019
        If you will redeem it, redeem it. But if you[[COMMENT(0)]] will not, tell
        me, that I may know, for there is no one besides you to redeem it, and I
        come after you.\u201D And he said, \u201CI will redeem it.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '4:4 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Boaz said, \u201CThe day you buy the field from the hand of
        Naomi, you also acquire Ruth[[COMMENT(0)]] the Moabite, the widow of the
        dead, in order to perpetuate the name of the dead in his inheritance.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '4:5 '
        content: 'Masoretic Text '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then the redeemer said, \u201CI cannot redeem it for myself, lest
        I impair my own inheritance. Take my right of redemption yourself, for I
        cannot redeem it.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  Now this was the custom in former times in Israel concerning redeeming
        and exchanging: to confirm a transaction, the one drew off his sandal and
        gave it to the other, and this was the manner of attesting in Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So when the redeemer said to Boaz, \u201CBuy it for yourself,\u201D
        he drew off his sandal. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then Boaz said to the elders and all the people, \u201CYou are witnesses
        this day that I have bought from the hand of Naomi all that belonged to Elimelech
        and all that belonged to Chilion and to Mahlon. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Also Ruth the Moabite, the widow of Mahlon, I have bought to be my
        wife, to perpetuate the name of the dead in his inheritance, that the name
        of the dead may not be cut off from among his brothers and from the gate
        of his native place. You are witnesses this day.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then all the people who were at the gate and the elders said, \u201CWe
        are witnesses. May the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> make the woman, who is
        coming into your house, like Rachel and Leah, who together built up the house
        of Israel. May you act worthily in Ephrathah and be renowned in Bethlehem, "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Ruth and Boaz Marry'
      title: Ruth and Boaz Marry
      number: 12
      content: "and may your house be like the house of Perez, whom Tamar bore to
        Judah, because of the offspring that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will
        give you by this young woman.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So Boaz took Ruth, and she became his wife. And he went in to her,
        and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave her conception, and she bore a son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then the women said to Naomi, \u201CBlessed be the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        who has not left you this day without a redeemer, and may his name be renowned
        in Israel! "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "He shall be to you a restorer of life and a nourisher of your old
        age, for your daughter-in-law who loves you, who is more to you than seven
        sons, has given birth to him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then Naomi took the child and laid him on her lap and became his
        nurse. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: The Genealogy of David'
      title: The Genealogy of David
      number: 17
      content: "And the women of the neighborhood gave him a name, saying, \u201CA
        son has been born to Naomi.\u201D They named him Obed. He was the father
        of Jesse, the father of David.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now these are the generations of Perez: Perez fathered Hezron, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Hezron fathered Ram, Ram fathered Amminadab, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Amminadab fathered Nahshon, Nahshon fathered Salmon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Salmon fathered Boaz, Boaz fathered Obed, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Obed fathered Jesse, and Jesse fathered David.
      comments: []
